The paper discusses a new line of boosting algorithms for multi-class classification, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a heuristic to overcome the computational limitations of prior abc-boost algorithms, which involves optimization and algorithm design (cs.AI). The datasets used in the experiments include Covertype and Poker, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning research (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the performance of abc-boost on large datasets, which involves considerations of scalability and efficiency (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the testing performance of abc-boost on a variety of datasets, which involves considerations of natural language processing and text classification (cs.CL).
